{
  "stem": "4753.10",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And then an airplane flew over the place where we were, dropping-- [PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] now I forgot, suddenly, the name-- anyway, leaflet telling to the German not to kill us.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And the German were telling us not to pick it up, the paper, but we did.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "So all the SS men, except two run away.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "The remaining two put-- ordered back to the train, and we were going all over.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "They didn't know what to do with us, but they didn't want to leave us behind, because they were afraid whoever will liberate that part, you know, because we didn't know, but they did, that the Americans were already there, surrounding them.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I think 1st of May, or 2nd of May in [NON-ENGLISH], when the Red Cross from Sweden came over and took us over and took us to Sweden.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I am speaking almost 20 years now to the-- with the Wiesenthal Center-- I mean, for the Wiesenthal Center.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I did go to colleges and schools, churches.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I did go to Sacramento to the Senate and to the Assemblymen.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I was-- spoke in there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I made many, many tapes, all free, all volunteer job.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I didn't do it for the money.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "For many-- I gave many interviews for newspapers and tapes, and so on.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The latest one is the '7th Heaven' TV show, who made an episode of hatred.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they did use a part of my life story.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They came to the Wiesenthal Center, or called the Wiesenthal Center, and asked whom they would recommend, a survivor, whose story should be filmed or written, because they wanted to write about hatred, and they wanted to have a survivor's, not an imaginary person's, story.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So they wanted to have an authentic people.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
